ions":["25","88","50","71"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\begin{array}{llcc}\\text { } & \\mathrm{N}_2 \\mathrm{O}_4(\\mathrm{~g}) \\rightleftharpoons 2 \\mathrm{NO}_2(\\mathrm{~g}) \\\\ & \\text { Initial moles } & 1 & 0 \\\\ & \\text { Moles of equil. } & (1-\\alpha) & 2 \\alpha\\end{array}$\n( $\\alpha=$ degree of dissociation $)$\nTotal number of moles at equil.\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& =(1-\\alpha)+2 \\alpha \\\\\n& =(1+\\alpha) \\\\\np_{N_2 \\mathrm{O}_4} & =\\frac{(1-\\alpha)}{(1+\\alpha)} \\times P \\\\\np_{N O_2} & =\\frac{2 \\alpha}{(1+\\alpha)} \\times P \\\\\nK_P & =\\frac{\\left(p_{N_O}\\right)^2}{p_{N_2 O_4}}=\\frac{\\left(\\frac{2 \\alpha}{(1+\\alpha)} \\times P\\right)^2}{\\left(\\frac{1-\\alpha}{1+\\alpha}\\right) \\times P}=\\frac{4 \\alpha^2 P}{1-\\alpha^2}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { Given, } K_P=2, P=0.5 \\mathrm{~atm} \\\\\n& \\therefore \\quad K_P=\\frac{4 \\alpha^2 P}{1-\\alpha^2} \\\\\n& =\\frac{4 \\alpha^2 \\times 0.5}{1-\\alpha^2} \\\\\n& \\alpha=0.707 \\approx 0.71 \\\\\n& \\therefore \\quad \\text { Percentage dissociation } \\\\\n& =0.71 \\times 100=71\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":28023,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{PCl}_5$ will increase","$\\mathrm{Cl}_2$ will decrease","$\\mathrm{PCl}_5, \\mathrm{PCl}_3 \\& \\mathrm{Cl}_2$ remain constant","$\\mathrm{PCl}_3$ will increase"],"answer":1,"solution":"On addition of inert gas at constant P \\& T, reaction moves in the direction of greater no. of moles so it will shift in forward direction, so $\\left[\\mathrm{PCl}_5\\right]$ decrease and $\\left[\\mathrm{PCl}_3\\right] \\&\\left[\\mathrm{Cl}_2\\right]$ will increase.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":28062,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>233</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math> of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>BaSO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math> contains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math> sulphur.</p><p>Amount of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math> in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math> of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>BaSO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>32</mn><mn>233</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>44</mn></math></p><p>So percentage of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi></math>&nbsp;in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>471</mn></math>&nbsp;of organic compound <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>32</mn><mn>233</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>44</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>471</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>42</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":28097,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Chemical Equilibrium","question":"","options":["<math><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>19</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>21</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>HCl</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8594;</mo></